commit.message:
Fix compatibility with `connection_pool 2.4+`

Fix: https://github.com/mperham/connection_pool/issues/172
Ref: https://github.com/mperham/connection_pool/pull/166

ConnectionPool descendants must accept `checking(force: true)`.

When it's called, all the cached connection should be checked back in,
and the `Thread.current` state reset.

Additionally, making `Connection` respond to `close` allow them
to be automatically closed on fork.
Switch assert_equal to assert_match to accomodate message.
Adds Ruby 3.2 to the CI matrix. Updates checkout action version.
